thingness that has been historically ascribed to blackness and that blackness enacts within, apposite to, and beyond the No One. No One bears witness to becomings beyond comprehension, making and unmaking monstrous forms of entangled future anterior life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aGerman literaturexHistory and criticismy20th century. 0aGerman literaturexJewish authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aGerman literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945), in literature. 0aPoetics. 0aPsychic trauma in literature. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / African American Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074331940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478021551zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478021551423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478021551/original  a978-3-11-074331-9  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles